# Storage Account network rules: default_action = "Allow" is required for
# Consumption plan (Y1) Function Apps deployed from GitHub-hosted runners.
# The runners are on public IPs that change per run, making IP-based ACLs
# impractical. Production with EP1+ plan and self-hosted runners would use
# default_action = "Deny" with VNet rules.
AZU-0012

# Key Vault network ACL default_action = "Allow": same reason as above —
# CI/CD service principal on GitHub-hosted runners needs data plane access
# to write certificates. Production would use "Deny" with IP ACLs for
# CI runner ranges or a self-hosted runner inside the VNet.
AZU-0013
